{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2f8e6623-e46c-4f2d-a2c2-aae7bb98bcff","content":"With Microsoft.Testing.Platform the CLI switches change names. The equivalent command is:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- \\\n  --treenode-filter \"/**/[TestCategory=Integration]\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\nKey mapping:\n\n| VSTest (`dotnet test`) | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|\n| `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` | `--treenode-filter \"/**/[TestCategory=Integration]\"` |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang --blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**Notes:**\n- Everything after `--` is forwarded to the MTP runner.\n- `--report-trx` requires the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` package.\n- `--coverage` requires `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`.\n- `--crashdump` / `--hangdump` require `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` and `HangDump` respectively.\n- The tree-node filter syntax (`/**/[Property=Value]`) replaces the VSTest filter expression syntax.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c3e11a12-6df2-4202-920c-d9d710388e6a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences with Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n- `--filter` becomes `--filter`(same) or `--treenode-filter`\n- `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` becomes `--collect-coverage` (with Microsoft.CodeCoverage) or you use a different mechanism\n- `--blame-crash` becomes `--crashdump`\n\n\n- `--blame-hang` and `--blame-hang-timeout` become `--hangdump` and `--hangdump-timeout`\n\nThe command invocation changes depending on the .NET version and SDK — with .NET 9 SDK or later, `dotnet test` integrates Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively, but for .NET 8 I need to clarify whether the project is using the newer test platform or still on VSTest.\n\nWhen using Microsoft.Testing.Platform, I can either run the test executable directly or use `dotnet test` with `--` to forward arguments. The argument mappings shift significantly: `--filter` expressions change to tree node filters for MSTest or stay similar for MTP, `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`, code coverage collection uses `--coverage` with format options, and `--blame-crash` maps to `--crashdump`. I need to clarify the exact syntax for the tree node filter when using MTP with MSTest attributes—the format should be `/**/[TestCategory=Integration]` to properly match tests marked with that category.","outputTokens":1151,"requestId":"0833:44A9F:7E2BDFD:8C62C79:69EABE7A"},"id":"055cb764-e08b-431b-9a9d-84bc2709ee4c","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:51:28.126Z","parentId":"d2ff7a5f-d00b-4f20-bbe8-857c6047512a"}
